# Restart Dev Services After Code Changes

Python microservices have **no hot reload**. After editing code, restart the affected process.

**Never** use bare `kill ... & uvicorn` — those die when the shell exits. Always use `dev.sh`.

## When to restart

| Changed paths | Restart |
|---------------|---------|
| `services/research/**` | `./dev.sh restart research` |
| `services/scripting/**` | `./dev.sh restart scripting` |
| `services/media/**` | `./dev.sh restart media` |
| `services/seo/**` | `./dev.sh restart seo` |
| `services/video-worker/**` | `./dev.sh restart celery` |
| `frontend/**` | Usually auto-reloads; `./dev.sh restart frontend` if stale |

Do this **proactively** after backend changes. Do not only tell the user to restart—run it yourself.

## Commands (from repo root)

```bash
./dev.sh start              # full stack + watchdog (auto-restart on crash)
./dev.sh status             # health check
./dev.sh ensure             # restart any down services immediately
./dev.sh watch              # start background watchdog (15s interval)
./dev.sh restart media      # single service (research|scripting|media|seo|frontend|celery|all)
./dev.sh stop
```

Services run in **detached screen** sessions (`cc-media`, etc.) with a **restart loop** — they survive terminal/agent exit and recover from crashes.

App URL: **http://localhost:3030**

Research cold-starts can take **20–30 seconds**. Frontend first compile may take **~90 seconds**.

## Verify after restart

- `curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://127.0.0.1:8003/docs` → `200`
- `./dev.sh status` — all services `up`, watchdog `up`
